THE GINGER MENACE. This year’s cocktail for Summer S’mores with Conan and the Chill Chums. Mix a batch and relax with your favorite chill chum. Enjoy!
.
• 1.5 oz. HAVANA CLUB RUM• 1 oz. APEROL APERITIF• .5 oz. FRESH LEMON JUICE• MIX CONTENTS INTO SHAKER • MICROPLANE .25 TSP. FRESH GINGER• SHAKE WITH ICE• POUR OVER ICE INTO CHILLED GLASS• ADD 1.5 oz. BUNDABERG GINGER BEER• GARNISH WITH MINT AND   GRAPEFRUIT POMPADOUR
.
#tradecraftcocktails

ALERT! ALERT! Come spend an easy evenin’ Mallwalkin’ ’n’ Townlandin’. Apostrophe overuse aside, this promises to be a banner night as Mark McConville and Matt Gourley present the first ever improvised Mallwalk, live without a mall! Then, Townland takes to their instruments in what may be their final performance for quite some time. Shannon and Wade are off to Texas for good and though one wouldn’t say this is the end of Townland, it may be the beginning of a long winter’s nap — who knows when next they’ll wake. To make this even more must-see, there will be very special guests, including Paul F. Tompkins, Andy Daly, and an assortment of top-notch musicians. In-person and live-streamed! I pray it doesn’t get OUT OF HAND. Link in bio.

IT’S KEYS TO THE KINGDOM DAY! Listen wherever you get your podcasts. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ 

Episode 1: Operation Petticoat and Episode 2: The Good, The Bad, and The Fuzzy are out now. Get all the behind-the-scenes stories of working at the world’s major theme parks delivered straight to your EARS. This podcast has been a long time in the making. Please enjoy. 

Keys to the Kingdom is an unprecedented, eight-part docuseries exploring the peculiar backstage life of theme park characters, performers, and fans. Hosted by recovering theme park employees Matt Gourley (Conan O’Brien Needs a Friend, Superego, Drunk History) and Amanda Lund (Earios Co-founder, The Complete Woman, New Girl), each installment promises insider secrets, stories of absurd guest interactions, and fascinating tales of workplace minutiae. Link in bio.
KEYS TO THE KINGDOM live stream Q & A.

The theme park fuzzy. Costumed head-to-toe in a fur-covered, foam-lined, portable sweat lodge. Why do they do it? For money? For honor? Matt and Amanda seek to find out as they talk to a menagerie of chipmunks, donkeys, and of course, mice. Link in bio.

KEYS TO THE KINGDOM EPISODE 3 • BREAKING THE RULES is out today. What about those rare theme park employees and guests that don’t dutifully follow the rules? On this episode of Keys to the Kingdom, we’re talking with the bad boys, the rebels, the wayward fuzzies and the defiant fans that stand up to the system despite the consequences. Guests include Nader Shokair, Rebecca Lumianski, Jeff B. Davis, Maria Blasucci, Sona Movsesian, Mark Felt, and Drew McWeeny. Link in bio.

All episodes of KEYS TO THE KINGDOM are available now! Here is my dad, Jim Gourley, on episode 8 • Happily Ever After. He met Walt and Lillian Disney when he worked there in the 50s. I didn’t realize until we did this podcast that I was a legacy Disney employee. What does that get me? Anyway, binge all 8 episodes now (link in bio) and all 8 bonus episodes are available on Acast+ (link in podcast show notes). This has been a labor of love about laboring at a place that you sometimes love and sometimes don’t. Thanks to all who participated for their truly wonderful stories and especially @amandafunbuns, without whom this never would have happened. Have a Disney day! (Gross.)

This was taken precisely one half hour before we got 43 Christmas colds, 12 flus, 8 meltdowns (3 of them mine) and 0 naps. But we did it together. 2024, I am all yours.
